p://dbpedia.org/resource/Nesthy_Petecio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nesthy_Petecio\"}, {\"begin\": 230, \"end\": 241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.9999999999399733, \"rank\": 5.960167412217888e-11, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paul Childs/REUTERS  MANILA, Philippines - An Olympic boxing gold remains elusive for the Philippines as Nesthy Petecio suffered an upset loss.\", \"from\": 302, \"to\": 445, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 331, \"end\": 342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.9999999999399733, \"rank\": 5.960167412217888e-11, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}, {\"begin\": 392, \"end\": 403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.9999999999399733, \"rank\": 5.960167412217888e-11, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}, {\"begin\": 407, \"end\": 421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nesthy_Petecio\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nesthy Petecio\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nesthy_Petecio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nesthy_Petecio\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Petecio concluded her Paris Games run with a bronze after a split decision loss to Poland's Julia Szeremeta in the women's 57kg semifinal at the Roland Garros Stadium on Wednesday, August 7 (Thursday, August 8, Manila time).\", \"from\": 447, \"to\": 671, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 530, \"end\": 536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.6991588441779113, \"rank\": 0.4162052678170083, \"text\": \"Poland\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 539, \"end\": 544, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_the_Elder\", \"score\": 0.9999980468761325, \"rank\": 1.952338419190739e-06, \"text\": \"Julia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_the_Elder\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_the_Elder\"}, {\"begin\": 658, \"end\": 664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manila\", \"score\": 0.9999999732401651, \"rank\": 2.6713332498517286e-08, \"text\": \"Manila\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manila\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manila\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eyeing a return trip to the final after baggingsilverin the Tokyo Olympics, the 32-year-old Petecio instead got nosed out by an opponent 12 years younger as Szeremeta hacked out a 29-28, 29-28, 29-28, 29-28, 28-29 win.\", \"from\": 673, \"to\": 891, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Petecio swept the judges' scorecard in the opening round, but the bouncy Szeremeta did enough to win the last two rounds as she advanced to the gold-medal match in her Olympic debut.\", \"from\": 893, \"to\": 1075, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I thought it was going my way this time.\", \"from\": 1077, \"to\": 1118, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I really believed that I would get it.\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1157, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the win was not given to us,\\\" said Petecio in Filipino in an interview with Olympic broadcaster Cignal.\", \"from\": 1158, \"to\": 1265, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1258, \"end\": 1264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cignal_TV\", \"score\": 0.710681350141283, \"rank\": 0.40707132284822717, \"text\": \"Cignal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cignal_TV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cignal_TV\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am still thankful because I fought well.\\\"\", \"from\": 1266, \"to\": 1310, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The loss denied Petecio of another encounter with Chinese Taipei's Lin Yu-ting, who advanced to the final amid a gender row that has swept the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1312, \"to\": 1464, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1370, \"end\": 1376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taipei\", \"score\": 0.9999985948255339, \"rank\": 7.791783806377232e-07, \"text\": \"Taipei\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taipei\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taipei\"}, {\"begin\": 1379, \"end\": 1390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Yu-ting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PeteciobeatLin three years ago in Tokyo, but the Taiwaneseexacted revengeon the Filipina in the round of 16 of the Asian Games last year in Hangzhou, China, on the way to the gold.\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1646, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1500, \"end\": 1505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.548454464072332e-14, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1546, \"end\": 1554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.999999354031824, \"rank\": 6.459685409028897e-07, \"text\": \"Filipina\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}, {\"begin\": 1606, \"end\": 1614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hangzhou\", \"score\": 0.9999999996039151, \"rank\": 3.960493424342271e-10, \"text\": \"Hangzhou\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hangzhou\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hangzhou\"}, {\"begin\": 1616, \"end\": 1621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.6272428655679474, \"rank\": 0.5647518941738683, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her exit also meant the end of the Philippines' quest in Paris for an Olympic boxing gold that has eluded the country in 100 years of participation in the Summer Games.\", \"from\": 1648, \"to\": 1816, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1683, \"end\": 1694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.9999999999399733, \"rank\": 5.960167412217888e-11, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}, {\"begin\": 1705, \"end\": 1710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999943384, \"rank\": 5.656487478362897e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eumir Marcial(men's 80kg) andHergie Bacyadan(women's 75kg) both dropped their opening bouts,Carlo Paalam(mens 57kg) crashed out of the quarterfinals, whileAira Villegas(women's 50kg) also snagged bronze.\", \"from\": 1818, \"to\": 2021, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1818, \"end\": 1831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eumir_Marcial\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eumir Marcial\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eumir_Marcial\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eumir_Marcial\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite the loss, Petecio joined an exclusive club of Filipinos who have won multiple Olympic medals, including swimmer Teofilo Yldefonso, weightlifter Hidilyn Diaz, and gymnast Carlos Yulo, and became the first boxer to do so.\", \"from\": 2023, \"to\": 2250, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2077, \"end\": 2086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.9999962193797799, \"rank\": 3.7806344344787325e-06, \"text\": \"Filipinos\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}, {\"begin\": 2143, \"end\": 2160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Te\\u00f3filo_Yldefonso\", \"score\": 0.9999999971239504, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Teofilo Yldefonso\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Te\\u00f3filo_Yldefonso\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Te\\u00f3filo_Yldefonso\"}, {\"begin\": 2175, \"end\": 2187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hidilyn_Diaz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hidilyn Diaz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hidilyn_Diaz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hidilyn_Diaz\"}, {\"begin\": 2201, \"end\": 2212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Yulo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlos Yulo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Yulo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Yulo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yldefonso clinched a pair of bronzes in 1928 Amsterdam and 1932 Los Angeles, Diaz won the country its first-ever Olympic gold in Tokyo five years after nailing silver in 2016 Rio de Janeiro, while Yulo bagged two golds in Paris.\", \"from\": 2252, \"to\": 2480, \"enti